bug.short_desc: Above sea level is in 'km' instead of 'm' in tooltip
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1202849 Wrong display
Description of problem: In the settings dialog the above sea level (ASL) is in meters (m), but in the tooltip the same number is suffixed as kilometers (km). See screenshots for details. I was able to reproduce this in Czech locale, I didn't try different locales.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): xfce4-screenshooter-1.8.2-6.fc24.x86_64
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Compare settings dialog and tooltip
Actual results: In settings dialog the number is in meters (correct), but in the tooltip it's displayed as kilometers (incorrect).
Expected results: Both displayed in meters.
Additional info:

Created attachment 1203090 screenshot from my system
That's very strange ..
See the attached screenshot from my system - it does seem to show the correct units.
What version of xfce4-weather-plugin do you have installed? the latest from repos?
I wonder if this is something that crept through in translation (typoish) .. likely?

Created attachment 1203373 Proposed fix
Yes, it seems it's typo in the translation. I think the attached patch is correct (but I haven't check it yet, I will check it later today.
Sorry about the wrong NVR in the report, copy and paste error from different bug :)
xfce4-weather-plugin-0.8.8-1.fc24.x86_64
The patch seems to also apply over the rawhide.
The proposed patch fixed the problem for me.
Thanks for the patch. I will push this soon (tomorrow most likely) and also submit this upstream.

Can you install this and verify that the patch has applied cleanly?
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/buildinfo?buildID=805859
Thanks.

(In reply to Mukundan Ragavan from comment #7) > Can you install this and verify that the patch has applied cleanly? > > http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/buildinfo?buildID=805859 > > > Thanks.
Thanks, I can confirm the build fixed the problem for me.
